  "title": "Question on the page \"connectCurrentRefinedValues\"",
  "body": "Hi! I have a documentation issue on InstantSearch.js. I could not find what I was looking for on the page \"[connectCurrentRefinedValues](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/connectors/connectCurrentRefinedValues.html)\".\r\n\r\nHi, I can't find a way to build a widget, which allows the user to clear all currently selected filters of one attribute. So instead of having eg:\r\n- Brand: Brand name 1\r\n- Brand: Brand name 2\r\n- Capacity: 50ml\r\n- Capacity: 100ml\r\n- Capacity: 150ml\r\n\r\nI'd like to render it like this:\r\n- Brand: Brand 1, Brand 2    xClearUrl\r\n- Capacity: 50ml, 100ml, 150ml    xClearUrl\r\n\r\nAny help on that topic?",
